Type Casting:-

public class name 
 {
     public static void main(String[] args) 
  {
      float a = 25.2f;
      int   b = (int)a;
      System.out.print(b);
   }
}

output:-
25  // Data is lost here as we converted float to int

Type Promotion :-

* Java automatically promotes each byte,short or char operand to int when evaluating an expression

public class name 
 {
     public static void main(String[] args) 
  {
     char = 'a';
     char = 'b';
     System.out.print((int)(b));
     System.out.print((int)(a));
     System.out.print(b-a);  // Here java directily considered b as integer and a as interger, and it can only be done in expression
  }
}
output:-
98
97
1
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
* If one operand is long, float ,or double the whole expression is promoted to long , float , double.
public class name 
 {
     public static void main(String[] args) 
  {
     int a = 10;
    float b =20.25f;
     long c =25;
     double d =30;
     double ans =a+b+c+d;
     System.out.print(ans); 
}
Output:-
85.25 // First Java converted all small data type into big data type that is double 



